# Material-UI (MUI) Component Standards

## MUI v7 Usage
- Use MUI v7 components from `@mui/material` package
- Follow MUI design system and component patterns
- Use emotion for custom styling when needed
- Implement responsive design using MUI breakpoints

## Theme Configuration
- Customize theme in [src/theme/](mdc:src/theme/) directory
- Use theme tokens for colors, spacing, and typography
- Implement dark/light mode support
- Use theme provider from [src/app.tsx](mdc:src/app.tsx)

## Component Guidelines
- Use MUI components as base building blocks
- Extend MUI components using styled API when needed
- Follow MUI accessibility guidelines
- Use proper MUI prop types and interfaces

## Styling Patterns
- Use `sx` prop for component-specific styles
- Use styled components for reusable styled elements
- Use theme tokens for consistent spacing and colors
- Implement responsive styles using MUI breakpoints

## Data Display
- Use MUI DataGrid for complex data tables
- Use MUI Charts for data visualization
- Implement proper loading states with MUI components
- Use MUI icons from `@iconify/react`

## Form Components
- Use MUI form components with react-hook-form
- Implement proper validation with zod schemas
- Use MUI date pickers for date inputs
- Follow MUI form design patterns
